<div class="row"></div>
<div class="row">
  <% cache("index_header", :expires_in => Time.new(Time.zone.now.year, Time.zone.now.month, Time.zone.now.day, 23, 58, 00) - Time.zone.now) do %>
    <div class="col-xs-12">
      <h1>Bringing You The Lowest Price For Any Supermarket Product<br/></h1>
      <h2>Since <%= @counter %> <% if(@counter == 0 or @counter == 1) %> Week <% else %> Weeks <% end %> Ago</h2>
      <h3>With a total of <%= @table_size %> products. </h3>

      <div class="row spacer"></div>

      <h5>
      <p>With this list, you should be able to gauge an item that you are purchasing at it's lowest price. <br/>
      You can now sort the list by any column in ascending or descending order. <br/>
      Filter is added for columns name, sku and aisle. You can input in the search field to display what you are searching for. <br/>
      In the discount column, if the price difference is more than 30% of it's original price,
      it will be highlighted in green, more than 50% with yellow. <br/>
      More improvements will be added in time.</p>

      <p>If you like this compilation, please donate to<br/>
      bitcoin address: 1JuNraU9vZyFxVqmUbTMJFFFFvzj1SHC48<br/>
      paypal address: daniel.ltw@gmail.com</p></h5>
      <div class="row spacer"></div>
    </div>
  <% end %>
  <div class="col-xs-12">
    <table id="products" class="display responsive" data-source="<%= products_url(format: "json") %>" width='100%'>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th class='all'>Name</th>
          <th class='not-mobile'>Volume</th>
          <th class='min-tablet-l'>SKU</th>
          <th class='all'>Special Prices (NZ$)</th>
          <th class='not-mobile'>Normal Prices (NZ$)</th>
          <th class='min-tablet-l'>Variance (NZ$)</th>
          <th class='desktop'>Aisle</th>
          <th class='all'>Discount</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</div>
<br>
